@Node 1 " Introduction "
What is BBS Rolodex?
--------------------

  BBS Rolodex is probably the most comprehensive BBS Lister Door you will
find for the MEBBSNET © BBS package.

  Features include:


a.  The ability to create a Rolodex-looking index card for every BBS

b.  The ability for the person who created it to delete it (as well as
    the sysop being able to delete it)

c.  The ability to  @{" DOWNLOAD " Link 12} the list right from the door, using various
     @{" COMPRESSION " Link 13} formats

d.  The ability for the sysop to  @{" CONFIGURE " Link 3} the door to use his local
    phone number format

  
@EndNode
@Node 2 " Why use BBS Rolodex ? "
Why use BBS Rolodex instead of other similar programs?
------------------------------------------------------


--- Frankly, there ARE no other BBS Listers as comprehensive as BBS Rolodex

--- It works!

--- Fully supported by  @{" LARRY CLOUD " Link 14} , a @{" MEBBSNET © CSR Site " Link 15}

--- Extremely @{" CONFIGURABLE " Link 3}

--- The ability to @{" DOWNLOAD " Link 12} the lists directly from the door

@EndNode
@Node 3 " How do I configure BBS Rolodex? " 
How do I configure BBS Rolodex?
-------------------------------

BBS Rolodex is an AREXX © script for the MEBBSNET © BBS software.  You must
already have AREXX © @{"installed and running" Link 16} prior to attempting to run this
door.

Once that prerequisite is met, you need to @{"make a MENU entry" Link 17} that allows
users to access it from a menu (you can't use @{"DOORS.CFG" Link 18}).

Then you need to make a subdirectory off of DOORS: and call it BBSROLODEX.
See your AMIGADOS manual if you don't know how to make a directory.

Next, bring the BBSROLODEX.CFG into a text editor (NOT a word processor!) and
edit the lines as applicable.  Press @{"This Button" Link 21} to see an example of
the configuration file for this door.  Make SURE you put the BBSROLODEX.CFG file
in your MEBBSNET:CONFIGFILES/ directory!

@EndNode

@Node 4 " What files are required? "
Required Files
--------------

All the files included in the archive are required.  If you are installing
this version as an UPGRADE, click this button @{"UPDATE INFO" Link 19} now, then
return here.

In addition to the files included in this archive, you'll need a copy of LHA,
ZIP, and UUXT.  If you choose not to use these compression formats, be sure to
edit the @{"BBSROLODEX.CFG" Link 21} file!

Be sure to @{"configure" link 3} the door to customize the setup for your BBS.

For program OPERATION, there is a file called (get this) INSTRUCTIONS.
This file is shown while in the door and the user asks for instructions.
Click on @{"THIS BUTTON" link 22} to read it.

@EndNode

@Node 5 " Updates "
Updates To BBS Rolodex
----------------------

You can get updates to this program at any @{"CSR Site" Link 15}.

@EndNode

