@Node 19 "Update Info"
What Has Changed In This Version?
---------------------------------

This is the place to look to see what has changed in this door.  It will tell you
whether you need to just install the executable (BBSROLODEX.REXX) or other
portions of the archive as well.  If this is the first time you have set up the
door, you MUST install the COMPLETE archive!

This version requires a new executable (BBSROLODEX.REXX) AND editing/replacing
the config file (BBSROLODEX.CFG).


Changes
-------


3.8
---

Added support for UUE encoded downloads.  You MUST have a copy of UUXT (NOT
included in archive) AND must edit your BBSROLODEX.CFG file.  See the example
config file.

Cut another 6K from the code size.


If you have a problem with the BBS Rolodex, be sure to send in a @{"bug report" link 8}.

See @{"HISTORY" Link 11} for info on previous versions.

@EndNode

@Node 11 " History "

3.7
---

Uncompiled version, forgot to take out references to the compiled stuff.  Also
forgot to include a CONFIG file!  Thanks to Don Bruce for pointing out the
error in my ways ;)

Shortened the code just a tad.


3.6
---

After much thought and complaints from many people, I have gone back to the
slow uncompiled stock Arexx script.  Fixed the reported problem in the re-
indexing of entries (I think, it works here, fingers crossed!)


3.5
---

3.4 worked GREAT on a local line, but froze up on a real line.  Still don't know
why.

I LOST the source code to 3.4 due to stupidity.  I copied the compiled version
(which had the same name) right over top the source.  So I had to take the previous
version, TRY to remember what I changed, and fixed a few things at the same time.
I would have had this version out sooner, but I had a hard time finding someone
with the source code.  I put a message in the echos but nobody came through.
Thanks, folks, I'm sure you really appreciate all the work I put into this.

You NEED to put the CONFIG file (BBSROLODEX.CFG) in your MEBBSNET:CONFIGFILES/
directory.


History previous to 3.5 has been deleted to shrink this file.

@EndNode

