@Node 9 " Other Programs by Larry Cloud "
What Other Nifty Neato Stuff Has Larry Cloud Written?
-----------------------------------------------------

Besides BBS Rolodex, Larry has written many small utilities and doors for the
MEBBSNET BBS package.  Some of them include (and are available at any @{"CSR Site" Link 15}):

--- Master Empire - Great Game - Arexx

--- Usage - Generates pretty bar graph of BBS Usage by Hour - ARexx

--- Callback - Small ARexx Callback Validation Door

--- MFB, CHT, & Goodbuy - Small Arexx FEEDBACK, CHAT, and GOODBYE replacements
    which allow the sysop to have more than one person available for feedback.
    Useful if your cosysop takes care of a good portion of the BBS operation.

--- FB & FREQB - Standalone FLO builder and FREQ builders in Arexx.  NOT
    doors, but handy utilities.


If you have an AREXX script that used to work with Starnet but no longer
works with MEBBSNET, I can help you convert it.  Contact me at Kitt's Korner.

@EndNode

@Node 12 " Download "
The Download Function
---------------------

Your users have the ability to Download the BBS List from this door.  There
are two versions of the list - the MINI and the VERBOSE.  The MINI has minimal
info, while the VERBOSE (or MAXI) has ALL the info the user entered on the card.
The internal DOWNLOAD function is called via the mebbsarexx.library, so if you
have a problem with this particular part of the door, theres nothing I can do
about it!

@EndNode

@Node 13 " Compression "
Compression Utilities
---------------------

This door requires a program that creates LHA files, UUE Files, and ZIP files.
These are not included in this archive.  If you choose NOT to support one or
more of these archivers, you MUST configure the door.  Bring the config file
(BBSROLODEX.CFG) into a text editor (NOT a word processor!) and modify the
corresponding flags.  Its explained in the config file itself.  Be SURE the
configfile is in the MEBBSNET:CONFIGFILES directory.

@EndNode

@Node 14 " Larry Cloud "
Who the Heck IS This Larry Cloud I Keep Hearing About?!?
--------------------------------------------------------

Larry Cloud has been dealing with computers since 1972, when he first got access
to a mainframe via a 300 baud terminal when he was in the 2nd grade.  The interest
in computers started there and grew.  He (its hard talking about yourself from a
third party perspective!) bought a Commodore VIC-20 for $200 when they first came
out, then bought a Commodore 64, then a Commodore 128.  His first BBS was The Charleston
Connection in Charleston SC, which was an instant success.  He then outgrew the
Commodore 128 and bought an Amiga 500, and ran a BBS on that (with no hard drive!)
for about a year, then spent $650 for a 20M hard drive.  He bought Paragon BBS
Software in 1991 and became one of the MANY Starnet Beta Testers.  During this
time, he became a beta tester for a rogue programmer of Starnet Utilities
named William Bowling.
Once William bought out Eric Drewry, the owner of Starnet, he took on the enormous
task of FIXING Starnet.  MEBBSNET is the result.  Larry has been a CSR since William
started the conversion (with a short recess due to a personal crisis).  You can
contact him at Kitt's Korner BBS, 206-698-0515 or 206-698-7760.

@EndNode

@Node 16 "Installing / Running Arexx"
Installing Arexx
----------------

This door REQUIRES the use of AmigaDos 2.04 or higher.  Since thats the case, AREXX
should already be installed and running in our system, unless you specifically took
it out of your startup scripts.  If thats the case, see your AMIGADOS manual for
instructions on re-installing AREXX on your system.  This door will NOT work
without the AREXX server being active.


@EndNode

@Node 17 "Menu Entry"
Whats The Menu Entry Look Like?
-------------------------------

You'll need to make an entry in one or more of your menus that looks like the
example below.  You can use any valid keystroke (I used Z in my example).

Option 'Z':
    Function Arexx doors:BBSRolodex/BBSRolodex
    end

Once you make this change, recompile the menu with MENUCOMPILER.

@EndNode

@Node 18 "DOORS.CFG"
Why Can't I Use DOORS.CFG for this door?
----------------------------------------

DOORS.CFG is not set up to run AREXX scripts.  You can ONLY run AREXX scripts from
a standard @{"MENU ENTRY" Link 17}.

@EndNode


